                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	Dehra Dun, July 25 (PTI): Nearly 200 women are killed every year in India after being branded as witches, a Dehra Dun-based NGO has said citing National Crime Bureau statistics.          
	Jharkhand tops the list followed by Andhra Pradesh, Haryana and Orissa. In the past 15 years, more than 2,500 women were killed after being accused of witchcraft, Rural Litigation and Entitlement Kendra chairman Avdhansh Kaushal said.                  
	Kochi (PTI): A plastic bag containing chemicals and giving out a foul smell was detected at Kochi airport before it was about to be loaded onto a Kingfisher flight to Chennai on Sunday, airport sources said. Inspections revealed that the bag, registered by a well-known courier firm contained boric acid and an unknown liquid.                  
	Madurai (PTI): Madras High Court has said that women schoolteachers working on consolidated pay cannot be denied maternity leave of 90 days. Teacher K. Sunitha had moved a writ petition after being denied maternity leave by the assistant elementary education officer.                   
	Chennai (PTI): A 64-year-old woman was attacked and killed at a mutt in suburban Selaiyur on Sunday, following which her alleged killer was lynched, police said. Satyaraj was caught and beaten up by local people. He died in a hospital.                                                                                                                                              
